# Testing Conventions

## Stack
- **Framework:** Jest 26 + Supertest
- **Location:** `server/tests/`
- **Types:**
  - `tests/integration/` — full HTTP round-trip tests against a real test DB
  - `tests/unit/` — unit tests for models, middleware, utilities
  - `tests/fixtures/` — factory helpers for seeding test data
  - `tests/utils/setupTestDB.js` — DB setup/teardown per suite

## Test DB
The test DB is automatically suffixed with `_test` (via config). The `setupTestDB` utility:
```js
const setupTestDB = require('../utils/setupTestDB');
setupTestDB(); // handles beforeAll sync, afterEach truncate, afterAll close
```

## Integration Test Pattern
```js
const request = require('supertest');
const app = require('../../src/app');
const { insertBasicUser, createBrand } = require('../fixtures');
const setupTestDB = require('../utils/setupTestDB');

setupTestDB();

describe('GET /api/v1/masterdata/brands/paginate', () => {
  test('should return 200 and paginated brands when authenticated', async () => {
    const { user, accessToken } = await insertBasicUser(['masterdata.brand.view']);
    await createBrand({ name: 'Test Brand' });

    const res = await request(app)
      .get('/api/v1/masterdata/brands/paginate')
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${accessToken}`)
      .query({ page: 1, limit: 10 })
      .expect(200);

    expect(res.body.data).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(res.body.data[0].name).toBe('Test Brand');
  });

  test('should return 401 when not authenticated', async () => {
    await request(app)
      .get('/api/v1/masterdata/brands/paginate')
      .expect(401);
  });
});
```

## Fixture Pattern
```js
// tests/fixtures/brand.fixture.js
const { Brand } = require('../../src/models');

const createBrand = async (overrides = {}) => {
  return Brand.create({ name: 'Default Brand', ...overrides });
};

module.exports = { createBrand };
```

## Mocking
```js
// Mock email service to avoid real SMTP calls
jest.mock('../../src/services/email.service');
```

## Running Tests
```bash
npm test            # run all tests
npm run coverage    # with coverage report
```

## CI
GitHub Actions runs tests on PRs to `main` that touch `server/**` with a PostgreSQL 15 service container.

## No Frontend Tests
Currently no frontend test suite exists. Do not add frontend tests unless explicitly requested.
